<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/9–143: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The British Minister Resident at Allied Force
                                Headquarters</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Macmillan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">British Foreign Office</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d557fn1">Printed from a copy made available to
                                the Department of State on September 1, 1943, by the British Embassy
                                at Washington.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-31">August 31,
                                1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have informed General Eisenhower.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>It is impossible to foretell the circumstances in which signature
                                if any is likely to take place and no arrangements can yet be made.
                                I <pb facs="1306" n="1192" xml:id="pg_1192"/> therefore trust that
                                the Greek Government will not send an officer from the Middle East
                                or anyone else for the present.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>In case of need I will telegraph direct to Leeper as you
                                suggest.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>